# Frontend Standards

Follow `.ai/rules/frontend-standards.md` and `.ai/patterns/react-page-pattern.md`.

## Invariants

- **Never call n8n, RabbitMQ, or internal webhooks from the browser**
- **Never enforce security in UI** — reflect API permissions for UX only
- **Never store secrets** in client code or localStorage (refresh token: httpOnly cookie)

## State Boundaries

| Tool | Use For | Never Use For |
|------|---------|---------------|
| React Query | Server data (cases, documents, API) | UI ephemeral state |
| Zustand | Modals, sidebar, filters, UI prefs | Server/cache data |
| URL params | Shareable filters, pagination | Sensitive data |

## Component Rules

- Server Components by default (App Router)
- `"use client"` only when interactivity required
- ShadCN UI primitives — do not modify generated ShadCN files
- API calls via typed client in `lib/api-client.ts` + React Query hooks
- Handle 404 gracefully for matter wall denials (do not leak case existence)

## Async AI UX

- POST returns 202 → poll `/api/v1/jobs/{id}` or subscribe to SSE
- Show "AI draft — requires attorney review" on unapproved summaries
- Reference: `.ai/examples/example-ai-summary-async.md`

## Accessibility

- WCAG 2.1 AA minimum
- Reference: `docs/12-ui/accessibility.md`

## File Placement

- Pages: `apps/web/src/app/(dashboard)/{route}/page.tsx`
- Components: `apps/web/src/components/{domain}/`
- Hooks: `apps/web/src/hooks/use{Feature}.ts`
- Stores: `apps/web/src/stores/{name}.ts`
